subSubSection.paragraph:
Distribution and natural history. This species is endemic to the dry forest of the canyon of the Marañón River in the Northern Peruvian Andes (
Fig. 3
) from Zapatalgo, Province of Utcubamba, Region of Amazonas ( 1029 m ) to Balsas, Province of Chachapoyas, Region of Amazonas, where it reaches its so far highest known distributional level ( 1037 m ,
Fig. 7
). The lowest distributional level of this species is found in Chacanto, Province of Celendin, Region of Cajamarca ( 852 m ).
